Your Journey Through Darkwind

A stage-by-stage walkthrough from your first steps to seasoned
adventurer. Each stage is its own short help page. Read them as your
character grows, not all at once.

help stage1: your first minutes. The tutorial, looking, and finding
your way around town.
help stage2: gear up and learn to fight, levels 1 to 5, while death is
still free.
help stage3: choose your path. Guilds, archetypes, and leveling.
help stage4: see the world, levels 5 to 30. Areas, wayshards, quests,
and what death really costs.
help stage5: money and craft. Banking, the market, and professions.
help stage6: find your people. Channels, parties, clans, and kingdoms.
help stage7: sharpen the blade, levels 30 to 100. Bosses, dungeons,
and uniques.
help stage8: renown and rebirth, level 100 and beyond. Hero, legend,
and the remort endgame.

At every stage: screenreader mode tailors output for you (see help
screenreader), "help list" browses every section, and the bug, idea,
and typo commands send feedback straight to the builders.

See also: help stage1, help basics, help screenreader, help feedback.
